{"_id":"NDAxYWZmYWY2YjA1","name":"Drive Off the Dragon","permission":{"default":0},"folder":"YTRkYWEyZmNiODM3","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":1,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":10000,"entryTime":0,"content":"<strong><em>Drive Off the Dragon.</em></strong> The ruins of Thundertree call to you. Your family and their friends once lived in prosperity there, and now they’re reduced to menial labor. The ruins are haunted by ash zombies, and rumor has it a dragon has made its lair in the Old Tower, but those are problems a hero can solve. Slay the dragon, or drive it off, and you’ll prove—to yourself and everyone else—you’re a real hero, destined for greatness.\n<section class=\"secret\"><p>GM Notes : </p>Human Fighter (Folk Hero)</section>","img":"modules/lmop-shared/journal/005_-_Player_Handouts/006_-_Quests/000_-_Personal_Goals/001_-_Drive_Off_the_Dragon/avatar.png"}
{"_id":"NGE4NzM0ZGMwNjAy","name":"Roll20 Note: Rollable Tables","permission":{"default":0},"folder":"MzJjNGJlZDhiZDJm","flags":{"R20Converter":{"handout-order":3,"handout-archived":false}},"sort":30000,"entryTime":0,"content":"We have introduced a feature to allow a GM to quickly switch between token images for the Dopplegangers in this adventure. <br><br>By right clicking on a Doppleganger token after dragging it to the VTT (or the named NPCs Vyerith &amp; Vhalak who are already placed) you can choose the Multi-Sided option to quickly change their token image via a scroll bar. <br>","img":""}
