{"_id":"gDOs3L2xPwLE8r5u","name":"Stonehill Inn","permission":{"default":2,"ODY1ZmU3OWIzNzY2":3},"folder":"uw1IkAt6OFHFUyZW","sort":100001,"flags":{},"content":"<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\">Stonehill Inn</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #191813;\">In the center of town stands a large, newly built roadhouse of fieldstone and rough-hewn timbers. The common room is filled with locals nursing mugs of ale or cider, all of them eyeing you with curiosity.</span><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" /><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" /><span style=\"color: #191813;\">This modest inn has six rooms for rent (</span><a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" data-entity=\"Actor\" data-id=\"NGMyYzJjZWNlZDFi\">Sildar Hallwinter</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">&nbsp;takes one).</span></p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p><span style=\"color: #191813;\">If the characters decide to stay here, see &ldquo;Food, Drink, and Lodging&rdquo; in the rulebook for pricing. (The characters&rsquo; other alternative for lodging is to camp outside the town, or to persuade a farmer such as&nbsp;</span><a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" data-entity=\"Actor\" data-id=\"NGU4Mzk4MzBiNTMz\">Daran Edermath</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">&nbsp;or&nbsp;</span><a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" data-entity=\"Actor\" data-id=\"MTVlZTQzOGEyYzNh\">Qelline Alderleaf</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">&nbsp;to let them sleep in a hayloft.)</span><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" /><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" /><span style=\"color: #191813;\">The proprietor is a short, friendly young human male named&nbsp;</span><a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" data-entity=\"Actor\" data-id=\"N2ZkZDZhYTAyNmVm\">Toblen Stonehill</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">. Toblen is a native of the town of Triboar to the east. He came to Phandalin to prospect, but soon realized that he knew a lot more about running an inn than he did about mining. The new town offered a good opportunity to become established. Toblen is upset that the Redbrands have been allowed to terrorize the town, and that&nbsp;</span><a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" data-entity=\"Actor\" data-id=\"NTMyNDYwOGVlYzQ5\">Harbin Wester</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">, the townmaster, has done nothing to curtail them. However, he tries not to stir up trouble for fear that the Redbrands might retaliate against his wife and children.</span><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" /><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" /><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Rumors:</em></strong><span style=\"color: #191813;\">&nbsp;Spending a little time in the common room and chatting up the townspeople can provide the characters with a number of good leads to explore in and around town. NPCs present in the Stonehill Inn and the rumors they pass on include:</span><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" /><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" /></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Narth, an old farmer: &ldquo;Sister Garaele, who oversees the Shrine of Luck, recently left town for a few days, then returned wounded and exhausted.&rdquo; (See the&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">&ldquo;Shrine of Luck&rdquo;</strong>&nbsp;section below for more information.)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Elsa, a gossipy barmaid: &ldquo;Daran Edermath, the orchard keeper, is a former adventurer.&rdquo; (See the<strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">&nbsp;&ldquo;Edermath Orchard&rdquo;</strong>&nbsp;section below for more information.)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Lanar, a miner: &ldquo;Orc raiders have been seen on the east end of Triboar Trail. The townmaster is looking for someone to run them off.&rdquo; (See the&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">&ldquo;Townmaster&rsquo;s Hall&rdquo;</strong>&nbsp;section below for more information.)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Trilena, the innkeeper&rsquo;s wife: &ldquo;Thel Dendrar, a local woodcarver, stood up to the Redbrands a tenday ago when they came by his shop and leered at his wife. The ruffians murdered him. Several townsfolk saw it happen. The Redbrands grabbed his body, and now his wife, daughter, and son have gone missing too.&rdquo; (Unknown to Trilena and the other townsfolk, the Redbrands took Thel&rsquo;s wife and children to their secret hideout.)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Pip, Toblen&rsquo;s young son: &ldquo;Qelline Alderleaf&rsquo;s son Carp said he found a secret tunnel in the woods, but Redbrands almost caught him.&rdquo; (See the&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">&ldquo;Alderleaf Farm&rdquo;</strong>&nbsp;section below for more information.)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Freda, a weaver: &ldquo;The Redbrands hassle every business in town, except for the Phandalin Miner&rsquo;s Exchange. They don&rsquo;t want trouble with Halia Thornton, who runs it.&rdquo; (See the&nbsp;<strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">&ldquo;Phandalin Miner&rsquo;s Exchange&rdquo;</strong>&nbsp;section below for more information.)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" /><span style=\"color: #191813;\">These leads should point the characters toward opportunities for adventure in and around Phandalin. In addition, any NPC at the inn can tell the characters that the Redbrands frequent the Sleeping Giant tap house at the east end of town&mdash;and that the ruffians are trouble.</span></p>\n</section>"}
{"_id":"tdzahHtDV1F10z7P","name":"Thundertree","permission":{"default":0,"ODY1ZmU3OWIzNzY2":3},"folder":"BUeYtiv4j7Fc74pl","sort":100001,"flags":{},"content":"","img":"modules/lmop-shared/journal/005_-_Player_Handouts/005_-_Landscape_Images/010_-_Thundertree/avatar.png"}
{"_id":"uMN3qbaVqRucXLHb","name":"Alderleaf Farm","permission":{"default":2,"ODY1ZmU3OWIzNzY2":3},"folder":"uw1IkAt6OFHFUyZW","sort":600001,"flags":{},"content":"<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\">Alderleaf Farm</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #191813;\">A wise female halfling of forty-five,&nbsp;</span><a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" data-entity=\"Actor\" data-id=\"MTVlZTQzOGEyYzNh\">Qelline Alderleaf</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">&nbsp;is a pragmatic farmer who seems to know everything that goes on in town. She is a kind host, and is willing to let the characters stay in her hayloft if they don&rsquo;t want to stay at the Stonehill Inn.</span></p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Carp&rsquo;s Story:</em></strong><span style=\"color: #191813;\">&nbsp;Qelline&rsquo;s son, Carp, is a spirited and precocious halfling lad of ten years. He is enchanted by the idea of being an adventurer and says that he was playing in the woods near Tresendar Manor when he found a secret tunnel in a thicket. A couple of &ldquo;big ugly bandits&rdquo; came out of the tunnel when he was there, and met with a pair of Redbrands. They didn&rsquo;t see him, but it was close. Carp thinks that the bandits have a secret lair under the old manor house. He can take the characters to the tunnel or provide them with directions to the location. The tunnel leads to Area 8 in the&nbsp;</span><a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" data-entity=\"JournalEntry\" data-id=\"ZjAxMTgyMWI5ZDk0\">Redbrand Hideout</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">.</span><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" /><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" /><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Quest - Reidoth the Druid:</em></strong><span style=\"color: #191813;\">&nbsp;Qelline is a longtime friend of a druid named Reidoth. If she figures out that the characters are looking for specific sites in the area, such as Cragmaw Castle or Wave Echo Cave, she suggests that they visit Reidoth and ask for his help, &ldquo;since there&rsquo;s not an inch of the land he doesn&rsquo;t know.&rdquo; She tells the characters that Reidoth recently set out for the ruins of a town called Thundertree, just west of the Neverwinter Wood. The ruins are about fifty miles northwest of Phandalin, and she provides directions so the characters can easily find the place. If the party pursues this quest, see &ldquo;Ruins of Thundertree&rdquo; in&nbsp;</span><a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" data-entity=\"JournalEntry\" data-id=\"YWFkZjA3OTAwOTdh\">Act 3: The Spider's Web</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">.</span></p>\n</section>"}
{"_id":"yogt6XrILSyPbl54","name":"Barthen's Provisions","permission":{"default":2,"ODY1ZmU3OWIzNzY2":3},"folder":"uw1IkAt6OFHFUyZW","sort":200001,"flags":{},"content":"<h3 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\">Barthen&rsquo;s Provisions</h3>\n<p><span style=\"color: #191813;\">Barthen&rsquo;s is the biggest trading post in Phandalin. Its shelves stock most ordinary goods and supplies, including backpacks, bedrolls, rope, and rations. The place is open from sunup to sundown. Barthen&rsquo;s does not stock weapons or armor, but characters can purchase other adventuring gear here, with the exception of items that cost more than 25 gp. (For prices, see \"Adventuring Gear\" on pg. 48 in the&nbsp;</span><a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" href=\"http://dnd.wizards.com/articles/features/basicrules\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Player's Dungeons &amp; Dragons Basic Rules</em></a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">.) Characters in need of weapons or armor are directed to the Lionshield Coster (see that section).</span><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" /><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" /><span style=\"color: #191813;\">The proprietor is&nbsp;</span><a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" data-entity=\"Actor\" data-id=\"NTk5OGIwMDFkMjI3\">Elmar Barthen</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">, a lean and balding human male shopkeeper of fifty years with a kindly manner. He employs a couple young clerks (Ander and Thistle) who help load and unload wagons, and who wait on customers when Barthen isn&rsquo;t around.</span></p>\n<section class=\"secret\">\n<p><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Delivering the Supplies:</em></strong><span style=\"color: #191813;\">&nbsp;If the characters began play with Gundren's adventure hook, their orders are to deliver the wagon of supplies to Barthen&rsquo;s. Barthen pays the agreed amount (10 gp to each character) and takes possession of the wagon and its supplies. If the characters tell him of Gundren Rockseeker&rsquo;s capture, Barthen is saddened by the news and encourages the party to find and rescue the dwarf. He considers Gundren a friend and was excited by talk of discovering the lost mine of the Phandelver&rsquo;s Pact in the nearby hills. If the party hasn&rsquo;t already learned details of the mine from&nbsp;</span><a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" data-entity=\"Actor\" data-id=\"NGMyYzJjZWNlZDFi\">Sildar Hallwinter</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">, a character who succeeds on a DC 15 Intelligence (History) check can relate the information from the first paragraph of the &ldquo;Adventure Backstory&rdquo; section at the start of the&nbsp;</span><a class=\"entity-link\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" data-entity=\"JournalEntry\" data-id=\"OTBjZDAyMjJmN2My\">Adventure Overview</a><span style=\"color: #191813;\">.</span><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" /><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" /><span style=\"color: #191813;\">Barthen also mentions that two more Rockseeker brothers, Nundro and Tharden, are camped somewhere outside town. Barthen hasn&rsquo;t seen them in a tenday and expects the brothers to return &ldquo;any day now&rdquo; to resupply. What Barthen doesn&rsquo;t know is that Tharden is dead and Nundro is a prisoner in the mine. See the&nbsp;</span><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\">Act 4: Wave Echo Cave</strong><span style=\"color: #191813;\">&nbsp;section, for more information.</span><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" /><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\" /><strong style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; color: #191813;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Barthen&rsquo;s News:</em></strong><span style=\"color: #191813;\">&nbsp;If the characters ask Barthen how business is going, the shopkeeper tells them that the Redbrands are making it hard on everyone, shaking down local businesses and flouting the townmaster&rsquo;s authority. If the characters seem of a mind to do something about it, he tells them that the Redbrands frequent the Sleeping Giant tap house.</span></p>\n</section>"}
